==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''*haliþa-'' ‘man, hero’, from Indo-European ''*kel-''.
Cognate with Old High German [[helid]] (German [[Held]]), Old Saxon [[helið]] (Dutch [[held]]), Old Norse [[halr]], [[hǫlðr]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hæleθ/

===Noun===
'''hæleþ''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''hæleþas''' or '''hæleþ''')
# [[man]], [[hero]], [[warrior]]

